1
00:00:34,214 --> 00:00:36,808
We are going so fast.
Aren't you scared?

2
00:00:37,150 --> 00:00:39,141
I'm enjoying it all the more now.
When you are with me...

3
00:00:39,319 --> 00:00:41,810
I'm not scared at all,
In fact, this is great fun!

4
00:00:43,156 --> 00:00:45,420
Watch it. You're going
to be really scared now

5
00:00:56,603 --> 00:00:58,161
what are you looking at?

6
00:00:58,271 --> 00:01:01,172
I feel like giving you a kiss.
- So give me a kiss

7
00:01:01,842 --> 00:01:03,833
Close your eyes first

8
00:01:04,344 --> 00:01:07,177
whenever you give me a kiss,
you make me close my eyes

9
00:01:07,547 --> 00:01:10,175
How will I know how good
you are at kissing?

10
00:01:10,350 --> 00:01:13,183
If you want a good kiss,
you got to close your eyes

11
00:02:32,799 --> 00:02:34,790
Hey! You've woken up!

12
00:02:35,335 --> 00:02:39,772
You speak as if this is the
first time I've ever woken up

13
00:02:40,273 --> 00:02:44,505
Because that truck keeps honking away,
I got to wake up early every morning

14
00:02:44,945 --> 00:02:47,880
why don't you keep that alarm clock
close to your own ears?

15
00:02:48,281 --> 00:02:51,273
You ought to thank that clock which
at least wakes you up on time

16
00:02:51,751 --> 00:02:54,743
Else, the whole world wants to fulfill
its dreams in the world of dreams itself

17
00:03:33,260 --> 00:03:34,420
Hey Maninder...
- Yes sir?

18
00:03:35,362 --> 00:03:39,128
Is everything okay?
- We've got to replace the carburetor

19
00:03:39,399 --> 00:03:42,664
Take the carburetor from the new car
and fit it in this one...

20
00:03:42,903 --> 00:03:47,033
and fit the old carburetor in the new car.
- Could you please explain in detail?

21
00:03:47,340 --> 00:03:51,003
Sure, I will. If you put
the carburetor of that car in this one...

22
00:03:51,344 --> 00:03:55,007
this one will work fine. And the car
that's here for wheel-alignment...

23
00:03:55,348 --> 00:03:59,341
will soon be back for a replacement
of the carburetor. You get that?

24
00:03:59,719 --> 00:04:02,017
Sure, I do.
- You've understood...

25
00:04:02,355 --> 00:04:04,152
but make sure you don't
tell Arav about it

26
00:04:04,291 --> 00:04:07,055
That's wonderful, Mr Vasvani.
What a con job!

27
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:11,626
We're here to fix cars
and make money

28
00:04:12,065 --> 00:04:14,795
So get on with your work.
Don't waste my time. Go on

29
00:04:16,303 --> 00:04:19,363
Go! Time is money

30
00:04:19,606 --> 00:04:25,374
Hey Ali-bhai...
welcome to my garage!

31
00:04:26,846 --> 00:04:31,442
Skip the crap! What silly jobs you do!
The cars get screwed in just two days

32
00:04:31,985 --> 00:04:34,044
Not again?
Here's what I'll do

33
00:04:34,387 --> 00:04:37,982
I'll entrust your car
to the real expert this time

34
00:04:38,391 --> 00:04:41,383
He has only to touch it
and it'll be fine. Okay?

35
00:04:41,561 --> 00:04:42,823
Arav...

36
00:04:46,466 --> 00:04:48,991
Have you fixed the car?
- This one can't be repaired

37
00:04:49,402 --> 00:04:51,870
It has a manufacturing defect.
Sue the manufacturers...

38
00:04:52,205 --> 00:04:54,400
you'll get a new car.
- But how do I know that you're right?

39
00:04:54,741 --> 00:04:57,073
What if I get stuck
in a legal battle?

40
00:04:57,410 --> 00:05:00,072
I've never made a false claim
where cars are concerned

41
00:05:00,413 --> 00:05:02,074
Okay? So don't you worry

42
00:05:15,595 --> 00:05:17,586
I have faith in my abilities

43
00:05:18,431 --> 00:05:20,422
Just wait and watch. There will
come a day...

44
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:24,427
when cars designed by me will
zoom across every street of the world

45
00:05:24,604 --> 00:05:27,437
That's tops, I say!
God bless you!

46
00:05:27,907 --> 00:05:29,238
"Sat Sri Akal, Papa-ji..."

47
00:05:29,442 --> 00:05:33,105
You've wasted so many pages
to write just a single line?

48
00:05:33,446 --> 00:05:37,439
Wasted pages? I'm writing a letter
to my folks, not wasting pages

49
00:05:37,884 --> 00:05:40,250
And, by the way, how do you
write a letter in just a single line?

50
00:05:40,487 --> 00:05:42,921
I'll show you.
- Go ahead. Let's see

51
00:05:43,456 --> 00:05:45,447
Here's the pen. I wanna see

52
00:05:47,460 --> 00:05:50,987
"I am fine here..."

53
00:05:52,265 --> 00:05:57,259
"and hope the same for you.
Your son, Arav"

54
00:05:58,138 --> 00:06:00,470
Is that a letter or a telegram?

55
00:06:00,874 --> 00:06:04,867
You won't understand.
Just mail it to my address

56
00:06:05,345 --> 00:06:08,075
You and I just don't think alike.
- Right!

57
00:06:09,482 --> 00:06:12,474
You've come to America so that
you can earn money...

58
00:06:12,852 --> 00:06:15,218
go back to India and settle down.
- Oh sure, that's spot on

59
00:06:15,822 --> 00:06:20,156
But that's not what I want to do.
Why should I leave the country...

60
00:06:20,493 --> 00:06:23,621
that's giving me everything?
Name, fame, progress... why?

61
00:06:23,963 --> 00:06:26,955
Don't leave it, sir!
Who's asking you to leave it?

62
00:06:27,434 --> 00:06:30,301
But do tell me something. What happens
of your folks back home?

63
00:06:30,537 --> 00:06:33,506
They'll be fine. My elder brother
is around to take care of them

64
00:06:34,174 --> 00:06:37,507
And once I get settled here,
they can come here and live with me

65
00:06:55,929 --> 00:06:59,023
Sir, my designs are truly innovative
and distinctively a class apart

66
00:06:59,532 --> 00:07:02,262
I seek your support to gain access to
the research and development...

67
00:07:02,435 --> 00:07:05,336
department of your principals.
- Mr Kapoor, you will have to find...

68
00:07:05,538 --> 00:07:07,529
alternative modes to access
the authorities

69
00:07:07,841 --> 00:07:10,207
I suggest you send in
your proposal directly

70
00:07:11,244 --> 00:07:12,233
Thank you

71
00:07:13,113 --> 00:07:20,212
Fab job Arav! You have turned
my car into a new one. What did you do?

72
00:07:20,553 --> 00:07:22,544
Nothing much, just a few
changes here and there

73
00:07:22,722 --> 00:07:27,557
You're so talented, why don't
you start a workshop of your own?

74
00:07:27,894 --> 00:07:30,260
If you say, I'm willing to invest.
- Mr. Patel...

75
00:07:30,597 --> 00:07:34,556
you want to throw me out of business?
- Mr Patel...

76
00:07:35,235 --> 00:07:38,227
my aim is not the opening of a workshop.
Basically I'm a car-designer...

77
00:07:38,605 --> 00:07:41,165
waiting for the right opportunity.
- And this is the land of opportunity!

78
00:07:41,574 --> 00:07:43,565
You don't know Mr Patel, Arav

79
00:07:48,948 --> 00:07:50,939
He's opening a new discotheque
very soon...

80
00:07:51,251 --> 00:07:57,190
to coincide with his nephew's marriage.
- I hope you guys will attend

81
00:07:57,590 --> 00:08:00,582
By the way, Arav, give me
a demo CD of your designs

82
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:02,591
I know a lot of people
in the car industry

83
00:08:02,762 --> 00:08:04,593
All right, sir.
- I have a piece of advise

84
00:08:04,731 --> 00:08:07,666
You ought to visit the gypsy temple once
and try your luck

85
00:08:22,982 --> 00:08:25,280
Look at them rocking!
Shake a leg!

86
00:08:27,687 --> 00:08:30,622
It takes little to make a Sardar
break into ajig!

87
00:08:30,924 --> 00:08:33,757
You get on with your luck!
I'm going to have a blast!

88
00:08:50,710 --> 00:08:53,076
You can keep this.
I'll take out another one

89
00:08:53,646 --> 00:08:56,638
Excuse me. It's not just
another piece of paper

90
00:08:56,983 --> 00:08:58,974
we both made a wish
and picked it up

91
00:08:59,352 --> 00:09:02,651
who knows? Maybe God wants both of us
to know the same thing

92
00:09:06,826 --> 00:09:08,987
"You'll meet with your destiny today"

93
00:09:09,996 --> 00:09:13,659
I can't believe this!
Are we each other's destiny?

94
00:09:14,667 --> 00:09:16,658
I don't believe in things
like destiny

95
00:09:16,836 --> 00:09:20,670
we reached the temple at the same time,
make a wish and pick up a chit...

96
00:09:21,007 --> 00:09:25,000
if all this can happen,
why can't we be each other's destiny?

97
00:09:25,778 --> 00:09:28,178
Because this is just a coincidence
and nothing more

98
00:09:28,615 --> 00:09:32,676
It's all about perception.
What if we meet again?

99
00:09:34,020 --> 00:09:35,282
We'll see

100
00:09:35,488 --> 00:09:39,015
Hi, I'm Anna.
- I'm Arav. Take care. Bye

101
00:09:41,628 --> 00:09:43,493
Anna! He's so handsome!

102
00:09:44,831 --> 00:09:46,958
Straight out of a romantic novel!

103
00:10:04,918 --> 00:10:07,648
"Girl you got me shocked
from the rhythm of your body"

104
00:10:07,887 --> 00:10:09,616
"Burn coz its hot
like wassabe"

105
00:10:09,822 --> 00:10:12,518
"Go low till you knock knees,
shaking that ass..."

106
00:10:12,725 --> 00:10:14,989
"till we crash kamikaze"

107
00:10:29,742 --> 00:10:31,733
"Take my hand,
make me turn around..."

108
00:10:32,011 --> 00:10:34,343
"put that flower-band
in my hair-bun"

109
00:10:34,647 --> 00:10:36,638
"Sway with me, lover-boy..."

110
00:10:36,883 --> 00:10:40,410
"you have married me,
now put up with my airs"

111
00:11:12,852 --> 00:11:16,583
"Love is real,
love takes time"

112
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:21,157
"Love is sinful
and divine"

113
00:11:52,191 --> 00:11:56,491
"Look up at me, my love.
Raise your eyes"

114
00:11:56,896 --> 00:12:01,265
"I'm a rare beauty, my love"

115
00:12:01,834 --> 00:12:03,961
"Take me in your arms,
hold me to your bosom..."

116
00:12:04,170 --> 00:12:06,502
"don't make me pine like this"

117
00:12:06,839 --> 00:12:08,830
"On my moon-like face,
apply a dot..."

118
00:12:09,142 --> 00:12:11,440
"embellish my beauty
with pearls and diamonds"

119
00:12:11,844 --> 00:12:13,675
"Drape me in a sari
that glitters"

120
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:17,509
"You have married me...
now put up with my airs"

121
00:12:23,856 --> 00:12:26,051
"watch me,
undercover cops can't stop me"

122
00:12:26,459 --> 00:12:28,518
"Gonna lock you down
with my lock and key"

123
00:12:29,362 --> 00:12:33,298
"Cause you could be Punjabi,
Gujarati, Parsi or a banging Bengali"

124
00:12:48,147 --> 00:12:52,311
"Youth is but shortlived, my love"

125
00:12:52,885 --> 00:12:57,288
"I just can't wait anymore"

126
00:12:57,690 --> 00:12:59,681
"My heart is pounding,
I'm beyond reasoning..."

127
00:12:59,959 --> 00:13:02,553
"fall in love with me"

128
00:13:02,895 --> 00:13:07,389
"Lay a bed in the room,
give me all the joy in the world"

129
00:13:07,767 --> 00:13:09,701
"Let your lips feed mine
the wine of love..."

130
00:13:09,902 --> 00:13:13,497
"you have married me,
now put up with my tantrums"

131
00:13:24,083 --> 00:13:26,074
"Your tight-fitting blouse"

132
00:13:26,919 --> 00:13:28,716
"Your flowing scarf"

133
00:13:29,021 --> 00:13:31,012
"Your skirt pulled up"

134
00:13:31,491 --> 00:13:33,584
"They drive me crazy"

135
00:13:33,926 --> 00:13:38,363
"They're others who dance
to your tunes, O pretty one"

136
00:13:38,931 --> 00:13:43,334
"They're others who do up
your hair-bun"

137
00:13:43,936 --> 00:13:47,599
"I'm one of those who don't
play up to women's tantrums"

138
00:13:48,274 --> 00:13:52,938
"I'm the love that makes
makes women bow at my feet"

139
00:13:53,646 --> 00:13:55,637
"win me over with your charms..."

140
00:13:55,948 --> 00:13:57,939
"come rushing to me,
whenever I call"

141
00:13:58,384 --> 00:14:00,443
"Give unto me your
youthful charms"

142
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:04,952
"Because I have married you...
don't show me those airs"

143
00:14:10,630 --> 00:14:12,621
"Take my hand,
make me turn around..."

144
00:14:12,965 --> 00:14:14,956
"put that flower-band
in my hair-bun"

145
00:14:15,301 --> 00:14:17,462
"Sway with me, lover-boy..."

146
00:14:17,703 --> 00:14:21,366
"you have married me,
now put up with my airs"

147
00:14:27,780 --> 00:14:29,975
"Love is the King.
You're the Queen of the party"

148
00:14:30,316 --> 00:14:32,648
"Feeding to have a scene
with this young hottie"

149
00:14:32,985 --> 00:14:34,782
"Have a ball,
take a drag..."

150
00:14:34,987 --> 00:14:37,717
"talk about the sex
and forget about the wedding"

151
00:14:55,474 --> 00:14:58,443
Arav, you look dashing
in this black suit

152
00:15:00,012 --> 00:15:01,001
Thanks

153
00:15:02,014 --> 00:15:04,676
I'm waiting for a compliment too

154
00:15:07,019 --> 00:15:09,010
Oh! So you are a shy guy by nature

155
00:15:09,455 --> 00:15:12,822
Anyway, this is our second meeting.
Do you think it's destiny?

156
00:15:14,026 --> 00:15:15,823
Mere happenstance

157
00:15:16,429 --> 00:15:18,420
There are just a handful of Indians
in this city...

158
00:15:18,631 --> 00:15:21,566
who keep bumping into each other
on festive occasions

159
00:15:22,435 --> 00:15:25,632
It'll be a mistake to call it destiny.

160
00:15:26,405 --> 00:15:28,635
There are hundreds of thousands of people
in this city

161
00:15:29,041 --> 00:15:33,478
So, our meeting again has definitely
got something to do with destiny

162
00:15:34,046 --> 00:15:38,039
Suit yourself with whatever beliefs.
- His belief, not mine

163
00:15:38,384 --> 00:15:41,046
You'll surely accept it some day.
- Well, it's that...

164
00:15:42,054 --> 00:15:45,046
wow! Friends already?

165
00:15:45,391 --> 00:15:48,383
Nothing of the sort. Just a
coincidence that we've met again

166
00:15:48,661 --> 00:15:54,065
My word! You need good-fortune for
such coincidences, my friend!

167
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,489
Bye!

168
00:15:58,971 --> 00:16:03,670
Dammit! What wrong have I done?
- I was trying hard to shake her off...

169
00:16:04,076 --> 00:16:06,067
and like an idiot,
you took up for her!

170
00:16:07,079 --> 00:16:12,073
What a nut! You don't try to
shake off gals like her!

171
00:16:13,019 --> 00:16:15,249
You ought to be chasing her!

172
00:16:19,025 --> 00:16:23,086
Anna, he should be crazy about you,
but he's just not encouraging you!

173
00:16:23,796 --> 00:16:28,529
Nams, some guys like it slow.
- Yeah

174
00:16:29,769 --> 00:16:33,102
Even I like it.
This is the way... slow!

175
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:37,100
But not so slow as to get old
and proclaim one day...

176
00:16:38,277 --> 00:16:40,268
"Darling, I love you"

177
00:16:42,214 --> 00:16:45,775
Nams, he might not agree
with me today...

178
00:16:46,185 --> 00:16:50,178
but one day he'll surely realise
that I'm his destiny

179
00:16:52,758 --> 00:16:55,659
That trip to the temple
and our second meeting...

180
00:16:56,062 --> 00:16:58,257
things like these don't happen
every other day

181
00:16:58,798 --> 00:17:01,460
I'm just waiting for
our next meeting

182
00:17:02,201 --> 00:17:05,136
There must surely be something that
will bring us close to each other

183
00:17:11,844 --> 00:17:16,611
Excuse me. Can I test-drive this car?
- Sorry, sir. It's only for display

184
00:17:18,150 --> 00:17:20,744
Can I check the interiors?
- With pleasure. All yours

185
00:17:27,493 --> 00:17:29,825
You...? Here?
- I am, wherever you are

186
00:17:33,599 --> 00:17:35,590
I'm sure you think this is
a coincidence too

187
00:17:36,602 --> 00:17:40,163
Actually I am very fond of cars

188
00:17:41,307 --> 00:17:44,174
well, cars are my life,
my passion... my destiny

189
00:17:44,677 --> 00:17:48,670
Destiny? Cars? So we do have
something in common

190
00:17:50,182 --> 00:17:52,844
It was nice talking to you.
See you again...

191
00:17:53,185 --> 00:17:54,982
if there is a coincidence

192
00:17:56,522 --> 00:18:00,925
Believe me, my destiny will surely bring
us together again. By a coincidence

193
00:18:11,804 --> 00:18:14,466
This car was launched only today
and you've bought it already?

194
00:18:14,874 --> 00:18:17,206
I haven't bought it,
I'm just taking a test-drive

195
00:18:17,977 --> 00:18:21,208
when I asked for it, I was turned down.
How come you got it?

196
00:18:21,547 --> 00:18:23,811
I'm well connected, you see?
You want a lift?

197
00:18:27,219 --> 00:18:29,710
What are you so thoughtful about?
C'mon!

198
00:18:30,089 --> 00:18:36,221
You are such a weirdo. Guys pray to
get a lift from a beautiful girl...

199
00:18:36,762 --> 00:18:40,220
and you are acting pricey.
- Okay

200
00:18:47,706 --> 00:18:49,901
Do me a favour, please.
- What?

201
00:18:50,242 --> 00:18:52,574
Give me my bag lying back there

202
00:18:56,582 --> 00:18:58,573
Here you are.
- Open it

203
00:18:59,118 --> 00:19:01,245
Excuse me, it's very unsafe
to open a lady's purse

204
00:19:01,420 --> 00:19:04,685
You won't be embarrassed. Open it

205
00:19:07,460 --> 00:19:09,451
Done.
- So give it to me

206
00:19:09,762 --> 00:19:12,128
Give you what?
- Give me the scarf in the bag!

207
00:19:12,431 --> 00:19:14,991
I can't see anything. Hurry up.
- Here you are

208
00:19:18,604 --> 00:19:20,265
what on earth are you doing...?

209
00:19:20,372 --> 00:19:22,602
We'll end up having a collision
while you're tying up your hair!

210
00:19:22,775 --> 00:19:25,073
God! Here's a harassed girl...

211
00:19:25,678 --> 00:19:27,873
instead of helping her,
you're yelling at her?

212
00:19:28,347 --> 00:19:31,680
Can't you simply tie up my hair.
Go on now. Do it

213
00:19:31,951 --> 00:19:35,614
Are you serious?
- Tie it up, I can't see a thing!

214
00:19:45,698 --> 00:19:48,690
What are you doing? Tie it up!
- As if I've done a course in this!

215
00:19:52,471 --> 00:19:54,302
Sit still, will you?

216
00:19:55,374 --> 00:19:57,103
Tie it up properly

217
00:19:58,310 --> 00:20:00,301
Thank you.
- You're welcome

218
00:20:03,382 --> 00:20:04,974
This is fun!

219
00:20:07,553 --> 00:20:12,650
Amazing body!
- It takes years for a body like this

220
00:20:12,992 --> 00:20:16,655
I can see that. But I've never
seen a shape like this one

221
00:20:20,399 --> 00:20:23,732
And this colour... it's a killer!

222
00:20:24,503 --> 00:20:27,131
I wish I could have it right now.
- What?

223
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:31,341
This car. I love its aerodynamics

224
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:37,781
Arav, what's your profession?
- I am a car designer

225
00:20:38,784 --> 00:20:41,947
If I get the opportunity, I could
design a better car than this one

226
00:20:44,623 --> 00:20:46,614
Anyway, you can drop me here

227
00:20:57,403 --> 00:21:00,065
when are we going to meet again?
- Whenever your destiny wants us to

228
00:21:00,706 --> 00:21:02,037
Take care. Bye

229
00:21:08,714 --> 00:21:10,375
My laptop!

230
00:21:12,949 --> 00:21:16,180
